@node "CanDo_SuperMover_Editor" "CanDo's SuperMover"
@toc "CanDo_Main"
   This tool lets you move groups of objects around on the screen in one
step.  The list on the left side of the requester shows all the objects
that can be moved; not all objects are movable.  To select an object simply
click its name; you can click and drag to select multiple objects.  A ">"
character will show before each object marked for movement.  There are two
menus to assist in selecting objects:  Toggle and Clear.  Toggle simply
unselects all selected objects and selects all unselected objects.  Clear
unselects all objects.

   The two fields allow you to enter the offset value to be added to each
selected object's origin.  These can be negative numbers, positive numbers
or zero.  To move an object down 25 pixels you would set X to 0 and Y to
25.

   Clicking on the Move button causes the move to occur.  If you hold down
the shift key when you click on the Move button the offset will be
subtracted from the origin instead of added to origin.  This has the effect
of reversing the last movement by putting all the objects back where they
were.

@endnode

